#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:269
msgid "### .mac"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:271
msgid ""
".mac files are ordinary text files that contain _Maxima_ commands. They can "
"be read using _Maxima_’s read command or _wxMaxima_’s File/Batch File menu "
"entry."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:273
msgid "One Example:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:275
msgid ""
"A .mac file named Quadratic.mac was created. It consists of two commands: "
"`f(x) := (x - 5)^2;` and `wxdraw2d( explicit(f(x),x,-5,15))`. The result of "
"entering that batch file appears below. (Some directory path information is "
"deleted.)"
