#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:343
msgid ""
"_wxMaxima_ is primarily a graphical user interface for _Maxima_. As such, "
"its main purpose is to pass along commands to _Maxima_ and to report the "
"results of executing those commands. In some cases, however, _wxMaxima_ adds "
"functionality to _Maxima_. _wxMaxima_’s ability to generate reports by "
"exporting a workbook’s contents to HTML and LaTeX files has been mentioned. "
"This section considers some ways that _wxMaxima_ enhances the inclusion of "
"graphics into a session. described here."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:345
msgid "## Subscripted variables"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:347
msgid ""
"if `wxsubscripts` is set to true variable names of the format `x_y` are "
"displayed using a subscript if"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '*   '
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:350
msgid "`y` is a single letter"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '*   '
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:350
msgid "`y` is an integer"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:352
msgid ""
"If the variable name doesn’t match these requirements it can still be "
"declared as \"to be subscripted\" using the command "
"`wxdeclare_subscript(variable_name);` or "
"`wxdeclare_subscript([variable_name1,variable_name2,...]);` Declaring a "
"variable as subscripted can be reverted using the following command: "
"`wxdeclare_subscript(variable_name,false);`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:354
msgid "## User feedback in the statusbar"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:356
msgid ""
"Long-running commands can provide user-feedback in the status bar. This user "
"feedback is replaced by any new feedback that is placed there (allowing to "
"use it as a progress indicator) and is deleted as soon as the current "
"command sent to _maxima_ is finished. It is safe to use `wxstatusbar()` even "
"in libraries that might be used with plain _Maxima_ (as opposed to "
"_wxMaxima_): If _wxMaxima_ isn't present the `wxstatusbar()` command will "
"just be left unevelated."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:364
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    (%i2)   for i:1 thru 10 do (\n"
"                /* Tell the user how far we got */\n"
"                wxstatusbar(concat(\"Pass \",i)),\n"
"                /* (sleep n) is a Lisp function, which can be used with \"?\" before. */\n"
"                /* it delays the program execution for some time (here for 3 seconds) */\n"
"                ?sleep(3)\n"
"            )$\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:366
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:720
msgid "## Plotting"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:368
msgid ""
"Plotting (having fundamentally to do with graphics) is a place where a "
"graphical user interface will have to provide some extensions to the "
"original program."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:370
msgid "### Embedding a plot into the work sheet"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:372
msgid ""
"_Maxima_ normally instructs the external program gnuplot to open a separate "
"window for every diagram it creates. Since many times it is convenient to "
"embed graphs into the work sheet instead _wxMaxima_ provides its own set of "
"plot functions that don’t differ from the corresponding _maxima_ functions "
"save in their name: They are all prefixed by a “wx”. For example `wxplot` "
"corresponds to `plot`, `wxdraw` corresponds to `draw` and `wxhistogram` "
"corresponds to `histogram`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:374
msgid "### Making embedded plots bigger or smaller"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:376
msgid ""
"As noted above, the configure dialog provides a way to change the default "
"size plots are created with which sets the starting value of `wxplot_size`. "
"The plotting routines of _wxMaxima_ respect this variable that specifies the "
"size of a plot in pixels. It can always be queried or used to set the size "
"of the following plots:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:379
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    %i1 wxplot_size:[1200,800];\n"
"    %o1 [1200,800];\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:386
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    %i2 wxdraw2d(\n"
"        explicit(\n"
"            sin(x),\n"
"            x,1,10\n"
"        )\n"
"    )$\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:388
msgid ""
"If the size of only one plot is to be changed _Maxima_ provides a canonical "
"way to change an attribute only for the current cell."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:391
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"     %i1 wxplot_size:[1200,800];\n"
"     %o1 [1200,800];\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:398
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"     %i1 wxdraw2d(\n"
"             explicit(\n"
"                 sin(x),\n"
"                 x,1,10\n"
"             )\n"
"         ),wxplot_size=[1600,800]$\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:405
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    %i1 wxdraw2d(\n"
"        explicit(\n"
"            sin(x),\n"
"            x,1,10\n"
"        )\n"
"    ),wxplot_size=[1600,800]$\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:408
msgid "### Better quality plots"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:410
msgid ""
"Gnuplot doesn’t seem to provide a portable way of determining whether it "
"supports the high-quality bitmap output the cairo library provides. On "
"systems where gnuplot is compiled to use this library the pngcairo option "
"from the configuration menu (that can be overridden by the variable "
"`wxplot_pngcairo`) enables support for antialiasing and additional line "
"styles. If `wxplot_pngcairo` is set without gnuplot supporting this the "
"result will be error messages instead of graphics."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:412
msgid "### Opening embedded plots in interactive gnuplot windows"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:414
msgid ""
"If a plot was generated using the `wxdraw`-type commands (`wxplot` isn't "
"supported by this feature) and the file size of the underlying gnuplot "
"project isn't way too high _wxMaxima_ offers a right-click menu that allows "
"to open the plot in an interactive gnuplot window."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:416
msgid "### Opening gnuplot's command console in `plot` windows"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:418
msgid ""
"On MS Windows if in _Maxima_'s variable `gnuplot_command` \"gnuplot\" is "
"replaced by \"wgnuplot\" gnuplot offers the possibility to open a console "
"window gnuplot commands can be entered into. Unfortunately enabling this "
"feature causes gnuplot to \"steal\" the keyboard focus for a short time "
"every time a plot is prepared."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:420
msgid "### Embedding animations into the spreadsheet"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:422
msgid ""
"3D diagrams tend to make it hard to read quantitative data. A viable "
"alternative might be to assign the 3rd parameter to the mouse wheel. The "
"`with_slider_draw` command is a version of `wxdraw2d` that does prepare "
"multiple plots and allows to switch between them by moving the slider on top "
"of the screen. _wxMaxima_ allows to export this animation as an animated gif."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:424
msgid ""
"The first two arguments for `with_slider_draw` are the name of the variable "
"that is stepped between the plots and a list of the values of these "
"variable. The arguments that follow are the ordinary arguments for "
"`wxdraw2d`:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:433
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    with_slider_draw(\n"
"        f,[1,2,3,4,5,6,7,10],\n"
"        title=concat(\"f=\",f,\"Hz\"),\n"
"        explicit(\n"
"            sin(2*%pi*f*x),\n"
"            x,0,1\n"
"        ),grid=true\n"
"    );\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:435
msgid ""
"The same functionality for 3D plots is accessible as `with_slider_draw3d`, "
"which allows for rotating 3d plots:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:450
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    wxanimate_autoplay:true;\n"
"    wxanimate_framerate:20;\n"
"    with_slider_draw3d(\n"
"        α,makelist(i,i,1,360,3),\n"
"        title=sconcat(\"α=\",α),\n"
"        surface_hide=true,\n"
"        contour=both,\n"
"        view=[60,α],\n"
"        explicit(\n"
"            sin(x)*sin(y),\n"
"            x,-π,π,\n"
"            y,-π,π\n"
"        )\n"
"    )$\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:452
msgid ""
"If the general shape of the plot is what matters it might suffice to move "
"the plot just a little bit in order to make it's 3D nature available to the "
"intiution:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:467
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    wxanimate_autoplay:true;\n"
"    wxanimate_framerate:20;\n"
"    with_slider_draw3d(\n"
"        t,makelist(i,i,0,2*π,.05*π),\n"
"        title=sconcat(\"α=\",α),\n"
"        surface_hide=true,\n"
"        contour=both,\n"
"        view=[60,30+5*sin(t)],\n"
"        explicit(\n"
"            sin(x)*y^2,\n"
"            x,-2*π,2*π,\n"
"            y,-2*π,2*π\n"
"        )\n"
"    )$\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:469
msgid ""
"For those more familiar with `plot` than with `draw` there is a second set "
"of functions:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: ' * '
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:472
msgid "`with_slider` and"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: ' * '
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:472
msgid "`wxanimate`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:474
msgid ""
"Normally the animations are played back or exported with the frame rate "
"chosen in the configuration of _wxMaxima_. To set the speed an individual "
"animation is played back the variable wxanimate\\_framerate can be used:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:477
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    wxanimate(a, 10,\n"
"        sin(a*x), [x,-5,5]), wxanimate_framerate=6$\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:479
msgid ""
"The animation functions use _maxima_'s `makelist` command and therefore "
"shares the pitfall that the slider variable's value is substituted into the "
"expression only if the variable is directly visible in the expression. "
"Therefore the following example will fail:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:487
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    f:sin(a*x);\n"
"    with_slider_draw(\n"
"        a,makelist(i/2,i,1,10),\n"
"        title=concat(\"a=\",float(a)),\n"
"        grid=true,\n"
"        explicit(f,x,0,10)\n"
"    )$\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:489
msgid ""
"If _Maxima_ is explicitely asked to substitute the slider’s value plotting "
"works fine instead:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:500
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    f:sin(a*x);\n"
"    with_slider_draw(\n"
"        b,makelist(i/2,i,1,10),\n"
"        title=concat(\"a=\",float(b)),\n"
"        grid=true,\n"
"        explicit(\n"
"            subst(a=b,f),\n"
"            x,0,10\n"
"        )\n"
"    )$\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:502
msgid "### Opening multiple plots in contemporaneous windows"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:504
msgid ""
"While not being a provided by _wxMaxima_ this feature of _Maxima_ (on setups "
"that support it) sometimes comes in handily. The following example comes "
"from a post from Mario Rodriguez to the _Maxima_ mailing list:"
msgstr ""

