#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:638
msgid "## Cannot connect to _Maxima_"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:640
msgid ""
"Since _Maxima_ (the program that does the actual mathematics) and _wxMaxima_ "
"(providing the easy-to-use user interface) are separate programs that "
"communicate by the means of a local network connection. Therefore the most "
"probable cause is that this connection is somehow not working. For example a "
"firewall could be set up in a way that it doesn’t just prevent against "
"unauthorized connections from the internet (and perhaps to intercept some "
"connections to the internet, too), but it also to blocks inter-process-"
"communication inside the same computer. Note that since _Maxima_ is being "
"run by a lisp processor the process communication that is blocked from does "
"not necessarily have to be named \"maxima\". Common names of the program "
"that opens the network connection would be sbcl, gcl, ccl, lisp.exe or "
"similar names."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:642
msgid ""
"On Un\\*x computers another possible reason would be that the loopback "
"network that provides network connections between two programs in the same "
"computer isn’t properly configured."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:644
msgid "## How to save data from a broken .wxmx file"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:646
msgid ""
"Internally most modern xml-based formats are ordinary zip-files. wxMaxima "
"doesn't turn on compression which makes the contents of .wxmx files viewable "
"in any text editor."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:648
msgid ""
"If the zip signature at the end of the file is still intact after renaming a "
"broken .wxmx file to .zip most operating systems will provide a way to "
"extract any portion of information that is stored inside it. The can be done "
"when there is the need of recovering the original image files from a text "
"processor document. If the zip signature isn’t intact that does not need to "
"be the end of the world: If _wxMaxima_ during saving detected that something "
"went wrong there will be a wxmx~ file whose contents might help and even if "
"there isn’t such a file: If the configuration option is set that .wxmx files "
"have to be optimized for version control it is possible to rename the .wxmx "
"file to a .txt file and to use a text editor to recover the XML portion of "
"the file's contents."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:650
msgid ""
"If the text file containing this contents is saved as a file ending in .xml "
"_wxMaxima_ will know how to recover the text of the document from it."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:652
msgid ""
"## I want some debug info to be displayed on the screen before my command "
"has finished"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:654
msgid ""
"Normally _wxMaxima_ waits for the whole 2D formula to be transferred before "
"it begins to typeset. This saves time for making many attempts to typeset a "
"only partially completed equation. There is a `disp` command, though, that "
"will provide debug output immediately and without waiting for the current "
"_Maxima_ command to finish:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:660
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    for i:1 thru 10 do (\n"
"       disp(i),\n"
"       t:makelist(i,i,1000000),\n"
"       length(t)\n"
"    )$\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:662
msgid "## Plotting only shows an closed empty envelope with an error message"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:664
msgid ""
"This means that _wxMaxima_ could not read the file _Maxima_ that was "
"supposed to instruct gnuplot to create."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:666
msgid "Possible reasons for this error are:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '*   '
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:671
msgid ""
"The plotting command is part of a third-party package like `implicit_plot` "
"but this package was not loaded by _Maxima_’s `load()` command before trying "
"to plot."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '*   '
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:671
msgid ""
"_Maxima_ tried to do something the currently installed version of gnuplot "
"isn’t able to understand. In this case a file ending in .gnuplot in the "
"directory _Maxima_’s variable maxima\\_userdir points to contains the "
"instructions from _Maxima_ to gnuplot. Most of the time this file’s contents "
"therefore are helpful when debugging the problem."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '*   '
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:671
msgid ""
"Gnuplot was instructed to use the pngcairo library that provides "
"antialiasing and additional line styles, but it was not compiled to support "
"this possibility. Solution: Uncheck the \"Use the cairo terminal for plot\" "
"checkbox in the configuration dialog and don’t set `wxplot_pngcairo` to true "
"from _Maxima_."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '*   '
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:671
msgid "Gnuplot didn’t output a valid .png file."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:673
msgid "## Plotting an animation results in “error: undefined variable”"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:675
msgid ""
"The value of the slider variable by default is only substituted into the "
"expression that is to be plotted if it is visible there. Using an `subst` "
"command that substitutes the slider variable into the equation to plot "
"(there should be an example of this in this manual) resolves this problem."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:677
msgid "## I lost a cell contents and undo doesn’t remember"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:679
msgid ""
"There are separate undo functions for cell operations and for changes inside "
"of cells so chances are low that this ever happens. If it does there are "
"several methods to recover data:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '*   '
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:684
msgid ""
"_wxMaxima_ actually has two undo features: The global undo buffer that is "
"active if no cell is selected and a per-cell undo buffer that is active if "
"the cursor is inside a cell. It is worth trying to use both undo options in "
"order to see if an old value can still be accessed."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '*   '
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:684
msgid ""
"If you still have a way to find out what label _Maxima_ has assigned to the "
"cell just type in the cell’s label and its contents will reappear."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '*   '
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:684
msgid ""
"If you don’t: Don’t panic. In the “View” menu there is a way to show a "
"history pane that shows all _Maxima_ commands that have been issued recently."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '*   '
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:684
msgid "If nothing else helps _Maxima_ contains a replay feature:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:686
#, no-wrap
msgid "    %i1 playback();\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:689
msgid "## _wxMaxima_ starts up with the message “Maxima process Terminated.”"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:691
msgid ""
"One possible reason is that _Maxima_ cannot be found in the location that is "
"set in the “Maxima” tab of _wxMaxima_’s configuration dialog and therefore "
"won’t run at all. Setting the path to a working _Maxima_ binary should fix "
"this problem."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:693
msgid "## Maxima is forever calculating and not responding to input"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:695
msgid ""
"It is theoretically possible that _wxMaxima_ doesn’t realize that _Maxima_ "
"has finished calculating and therefore never gets informed it can send new "
"data to _Maxima_. If this is the case “Trigger evaluation” might "
"resynchronize the two programs."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:697
msgid "## My SBCL-based _Maxima_ runs out of memory"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:699
msgid ""
"SBCL by default comes with a memory limit that allows it to run even on low-"
"end computers. When compiling a big software package like lapack or dealing "
"with extremely big lists or equations this limit might be too low. In order "
"to extend the limits sbcl can be provided with the command line parameter `--"
"dynamic-space-size` that tells sbcl how many megabytes it should reserve. A "
"32bit-windows-sbcl can reserve up to 999 Megabytes, 1800. A 64-bit sbcl "
"version running on windows can be instructed to use more than the about 1280 "
"Megabytes compiling lapack needs."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /home/dauti/Software/wxmaxima/info/wxmaxima.md:701
msgid ""
"One way to provide _maxima_ (and thus sbcl) with command line parameters is "
"the \"Additional parameters for Maxima\" field of _wxMaxima_’s configuration "
"dialogue."
msgstr ""

